<p><strong>Question 1: What is the Steel Designers Handbook?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The Steel Designers Handbook is a comprehensive reference guide for steel designers, architects, engineers, and students. It provides detailed information on all aspects of steel design, from material properties to design methods.</p>
<p><strong>Question 2: What are the new features of the 8th edition?</strong></p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The 8th edition of the Steel Designers Handbook includes several new features, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Updated chapters on seismic design, sustainability, and Eurocodes</li>
<li>New sections on composite construction, cold-formed steel, and stainless steel</li>
<li>Expanded coverage of fire protection, fatigue, and welding</li>
</ul>
